# Flint — Performance & Observability

## NFR Targets (Treat as Tests)

| Requirement | Target | CI Gate |
|---|---|---|
| Directional TTFT P95 | < 800ms | Fail PR > 900ms |
| Depth response fully streamed P95 | < 8s | Warn |
| RAG retrieval (sqlite-vec) P95 | < 50ms | Fail PR > 60ms |
| Transcription lag P95 | < 2s | Fail PR > 2.5s |
| Question detection P95 | ≤ 100ms | Auto-bypass classifier > 200ms rolling |
| App cold start P95 | < 3s | Warn > 4s |
| RNNoise per frame | < 5ms | — |
| Pre-warm cache threshold | 0.85 cosine | — |
| RAG top-k | 8–10 chunks after MMR de-dup | — |

Any code path that cannot meet these targets is wrong by definition.

## Context Budget Allocation (Every LLM Call)

```
Total = provider_context_window × 0.6
RAG chunks:           40% of budget
Conversation history: 40% of budget
System prompt:        10% of budget
Current question:     10% of budget
```

Budget edge case (question + min system prompt + min RAG > window):
1. Trim RAG to minimum 2 chunks.
2. Drop oldest conversational turns.
3. Keep current question and system prompt intact.
4. Emit `context_truncated` observability event.

## Structured Logging Schema (Mandatory for Every LLM Request)

```json
{
  "timestamp": "ISO8601",
  "level": "INFO",
  "service": "orchestrator",
  "session_id": "uuid",
  "event": "directional_thread_complete",
  "ttft_ms": 412,
  "provider": "groq",
  "model": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
  "cache_hit": false,
  "confidence": 0.82
}
```

Per-request metrics emitted on every LLM call: `provider`, `model`, `thread_type` (directional/depth/clarifying/detection), `ttft_ms`, `stream_complete_ms`, `rag_latency_ms`, `cache_hit`, `confidence_score`, `tokens_input`, `tokens_output`, `failover_triggered`.

## Log Levels

| Level | When to use |
|---|---|
| ERROR | Production incidents requiring immediate attention |
| WARN | Degraded performance (TTFT > 1s, RAG > 60ms, fallback triggered) |
| INFO | Lifecycle events (session start/end, state transitions, provider switch) |
| DEBUG | Development only — compiled out in release builds (`#[cfg(debug_assertions)]`) |

## Local Metrics

- Written to `~/.flint/metrics.log`. Rotated daily. Retained 7 days locally.
- Uploaded to telemetry endpoint on user opt-in (**off by default**).

## Debug Dashboard (Dev Builds Only)

Local web dashboard at `http://localhost:7373` showing: live TTFT, cache hit rate, confidence distribution, thread health, provider rate limit status, recent error log.

## User-Facing Performance Alerts

| Condition | UI Signal |
|---|---|
| TTFT > 1s directional | Amber indicator on panel |
| TTFT > 2s directional | Orange indicator + tooltip |
| Provider 429 rate limit | "Approaching free tier limit" toast |
| Failover triggered | "Running locally" indicator |
| Transcription lag > 2s | "Audio processing slow" amber indicator |

## Prompts Are First-Class Artifacts

- All prompts live in `/prompts/` versioned by directory.
- Every prompt has three variants: `gpt.txt`, `claude.txt`, `llama.txt`.
- A prompt change REQUIRES an eval harness run before merging.
- Regression gate: win rate ≥ 50%, directional conciseness pass rate ≥ 95%, no domain score below 0.7 relevance.
- NEVER inline a prompt as a Rust string literal. Always load from `/prompts/`.
- Template variables: `{rag_chunks}`, `{rolling_summary_if_compressed}`, `{last_n_turns}`, `{question}`, `{session_domain}`, `{interviewer_role}`, `{interviewer_priorities}`, `{utterance}`, `{pasted_context}`, `{old_turns}`, `{full_transcript}`.
